<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="German2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">German,</orth> adj. pertaining to Germany: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 48</bibl>. <cit><quote>like a G. clock, still a repairing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.192" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 192</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the G. hunting in water-work,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 157</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a full acorned boar, a G. one,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.5.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 5, 16</bibl></cit> (O. Edd. <emph>Jarmen</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>